---
import RealestateLayout from '../../../layouts/RealestateLayout.astro';
import CtaButton from '../../../components/CtaButton.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../../../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<RealestateLayout
  title="GTA Real Estate Market Update: May 2026 | Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent"
  description="GTA real estate market updates, trends, and insights from Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent at Trustwell Realty Inc., Brokerage."
  canonicalPath="/market-updates"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>GTA Market Updates</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__subtitle">
        Regular insights on Greater Toronto Area real estate trends, pricing data,
        and neighbourhood developments to help you make informed decisions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="report">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="report__content">
        <header class="report__header">
          <h2>GTA Real Estate Market Update: May 2026</h2>
          <p class="report__byline">Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent | Trustwell Realty Inc., Brokerage</p>
        </header>

        <p>
          The spring market arrived in the GTA with mixed signals. Sales volume in April came
          in below the 10-year average for the month. Inventory grew. That combination shifted
          negotiating leverage toward buyers in much of the region.
        </p>
        <p>Here's what the numbers show for Toronto, Markham, and Richmond Hill.</p>

        <h3>Price Trends</h3>
        <p>
          GTA benchmark prices in April 2026 held relatively flat month-over-month, continuing
          a period of stability following two years of adjustment from the 2022 peak.
          Year-over-year, prices are modestly below April 2025, though the gap has narrowed
          since the start of the year.
        </p>
        <p>
          In Markham and Richmond Hill, detached homes drew steady interest from move-up buyers.
          Prices in these markets have been more resilient than the broader Toronto average,
          supported by demand from buyers priced out of inner Toronto.
        </p>
        <p>
          In Toronto proper, the condo segment saw the sharpest softness. New listings outpaced
          sales in April, pushing months of inventory above the balanced range. Sellers in this
          segment face more competition.
        </p>

        <h3>Inventory and Days on Market</h3>
        <p>
          Active listings across the GTA are up approximately 25 percent year-over-year. Months
          of inventory, a measure of how long it would take to sell all active listings at the
          current pace, sits above 3 months for detached homes and above 4 months for condos.
          A balanced market typically falls between 4 and 6 months.
        </p>
        <p>
          Properties priced correctly are still selling. The average days on market for sold
          properties in April was 18 days, in line with the past three months. Overpriced
          listings are sitting longer and often see price reductions before selling.
        </p>

        <h3>What This Means for Buyers</h3>
        <p>
          Buyers have more time and more options than they did a year ago. Multiple-offer
          situations still occur, particularly for well-priced detached homes in Markham and
          Richmond Hill. The frantic conditions of 2020 to 2022 are not present. If you're
          searching now, prepare your financing, define your criteria, and move when the right
          property appears.
        </p>

        <h3>What This Means for Sellers</h3>
        <p>
          Pricing accurately from day one matters more than it did when the market absorbed
          everything. A well-prepared home at the right price will sell. An overpriced listing
          accumulates days on market and typically receives a lower final sale price than a
          correctly-priced listing would have.
        </p>

        <h3>Looking Ahead</h3>
        <p>
          The Bank of Canada's rate decisions through the summer will affect the market. Lower
          borrowing costs tend to bring more buyers to the table. Whether conditions shift
          before fall depends on inflation data in May and June.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you're thinking about buying or selling in the GTA this year, book a consultation.
          I'll give you a clear picture of what's happening in your specific area.
        </p>

        <div class="report__cta">
          <CtaButton href="/contact" label="Book a Consultation" variant="primary" />
        </div>

        <p class="report__disclaimer">
          Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent. Real estate services provided through Trustwell Realty
          Inc., Brokerage. This report reflects publicly available market data and Cory's
          interpretation of current conditions. It is not a guarantee of future performance or
          value.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <NewsletterSignup heading="Get Market Updates in Your Inbox" />
</RealestateLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-hero__subtitle {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 34rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .report {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .report__content {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .report__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .report__header h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .report__byline {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .report__content h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .report__content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .report__cta {
    text-align: center;
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .report__disclaimer {
    font-size: 0.8125rem !important;
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-style: italic;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
</style>
